lead_paragraph: The U. S. Mail steamship Empire City, Capt. TANNER, arrived at this port at an early hour yesterday morning, from New-Orleans and Havana, bringing dates from the latter port to the 2d inst. The Empire City brings 150 passengers, and $350,000 in gold-dust, of which $100,000 is consigned to Drew, Robinson Co., and the remainder in the hands of passengers.

headline.main: LATER FROM HAVANA.; ARRIVAL OF THE EMPIRE CITY. $350,000 IN GOLD. CUBAN PRISONERS SENT TO SPAIN. ALL QUIET IN CUBA. Commercial Affairs.
